The Senate has passed a bill to establish the Federal University of Technology, Auchi, Edo State. This followed its re-commital to the Committee of the Whole on Tuesday in a motion sponsored by Senator Yahaya Abdullahi (Kebbi North). In his presentation, Senator Abdullahi, recalled that the Federal University of Technology, Auchi, Edo (Establishment) Bill was passed by the National Assembly and transmitted to the President for assent. He said, “some fundamental issues which require fresh legislative action by both Chambers of the National Assembly emerged after critical analysis of the Bill by Mr. President C-in-C.” Against this backdrop, he added that a Technical Committee of the Senate and House of Representatives and Directorate of Legal Services met and worked on the Bill. Hence, relying on order 1(b) and order 52(6) of the Senate Standing Order, 2022 as amended, the Upper Chamber while rescinded its decision on the bill and re-committed same to the Committee of the While for re-consideration and passage.